            <div class="section-title">Code of Conduct for Teachers</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph">
                A code of conduct for teachers outlines the professional standards and expectations that educators should adhere to in their interactions with students, colleagues, and the College community.
            </div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Professionalism:</strong> Teachers should treat all students, parents, colleagues, and staff with respect, dignity, and fairness. They should recognize and value the diversity of individuals and cultures within the school community.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Respect:</strong> Teachers should prioritize the physical, emotional, and mental well-being of their students. They should create a safe and inclusive learning environment that promotes student engagement, respect, and positive relationships.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Professional development:</strong> Teachers should engage in continuous professional development to enhance their knowledge, skills, and teaching practices. They should stay informed about new educational research, methodologies, and technologies to improve student learning outcomes.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Communication:</strong> Teachers should communicate effectively and respectfully with students, parents, colleagues, and other stakeholders. They should listen actively, provide constructive feedback, and encourage open and honest dialogue.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Boundaries:</strong> Teachers should establish appropriate professional boundaries with students to maintain a safe and supportive learning environment. They should avoid engaging in any behavior that may be perceived as inappropriate or harmful.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Compliance with policies and regulations:</strong> Teachers should adhere to all relevant policies, laws, and regulations governing education, including those related to student discipline, grading, assessment, and reporting.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Collaboration and teamwork:</strong> Teachers should collaborate with colleagues, administrators, and other professionals to improve teaching practices, curriculum development, and student support services. They should foster a positive and inclusive working environment.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Role modeling:</strong> Teachers should serve as positive role models for their students by demonstrating ethical behavior, responsible decision-making, and a commitment to lifelong learning.</div>

            <div class="section-title">Code of Conduct for Students</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph">
                A code of conduct sets forth the expectations and standards of behavior that students should uphold while attending college. These codes are designed to promote a safe, inclusive, and respectful environment for learning and personal growth.
            </div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Academic integrity:</strong> Students should maintain high standards of academic honesty and integrity. They should not engage in plagiarism, cheating, or any form of academic dishonesty. They should submit their own work and give proper credit to sources used in their academic pursuits.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Respect for others:</strong> Students should treat all members of the college community with respect, dignity, and fairness. They should not engage in discrimination, harassment, bullying, or any behavior that infringes upon the rights or well-being of others. This includes respecting diverse backgrounds, cultures, beliefs, and opinions.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Personal responsibility:</strong> Students are expected to take responsibility for their actions and choices. This includes attending classes regularly, completing assignments on time, and actively participating in their educational pursuits. Students should also take responsibility for their personal well-being and make informed decisions regarding their physical and mental health.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Respect for property:</strong> Students should respect and take care of college property, including facilities, equipment, and resources. They should not engage in vandalism, theft, or any actions that could damage or misuse college property.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Alcohol and drug use:</strong> Students should comply with local laws and college policies regarding alcohol and drug use. They should refrain from engaging in illegal activities, underage drinking, or using illicit substances on college premises.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Safety and security:</strong> Students should prioritize the safety and security of themselves and others. They should follow college safety guidelines, report any safety concerns, and not engage in behavior that jeopardizes the well-being of the college community.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Digital etiquette:</strong> Students should adhere to appropriate online behavior and digital etiquette. This includes respecting others' privacy, refraining from cyberbullying, and using technology in a responsible and respectful manner.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Compliance with college policies:</strong> Students should familiarize themselves with and adhere to all college policies and regulations. This includes policies related to student conduct, use of college resources, parking, and any other guidelines set forth by the institution.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Community involvement:</strong> Students should actively contribute to the college community by participating in extracurricular activities, engaging in positive social interactions, and supporting a sense of belonging among their peers.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Conflict resolution:</strong> Students should seek to resolve conflicts and disagreements in a respectful and constructive manner. They should utilize appropriate channels for conflict resolution, such as mediation or seeking guidance from college advisors or administrators.</div>
            <div class="content-paragraph"><strong>Environment consciousness:</strong> Students should refrain from the use of plastics thereby keeping the campus clean and green.</div>
